721085f.title: Manhattan: Lexington Avenue - 91st Street (East)
721085f.text:
1389-91 Lexington Ave., east side, between East 91st and 92nd Streets.
Upon the excavation that appears partially,was constructed the 11-story
building occupied by the Y.M.H.A. This edifice is at the S.E. corner of
East 92nd Street and did not include brownstone houses shown. This
set consists of a negative and a positive.
November 10, 1928.
F. M. Demarest..
Gift of Albert A. Volk Co.
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE ON ALL REPRODUCTIONS.

721083f-c.title: Manhattan: Lexington Avenue - 91st Street (East)
721083f-c.text:
Lexington Ave., east side, north from East 91st Street. The row
of low structures seen bear No's 1381 to 1391 inclusive and are at the
N.E. corner of this point. No. 3 shows this feature as viewed frontally.
(Overshadowing same is the Y.M.H.A. at the S.E. corner of 92nd Street.
No. 2 shows the latter on the extreme right with modern apartment houses
to the north.
August 13, 1937.
Dift of Geo. D. Chinn.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
